results.name: a(n) = A193507(n) - A080359(n).
comment: The places of nonzero terms correspond to places of those terms of A193507 which are in A164294. Conjecture: The asymptotic density of nonzero terms is 2/(e^2+1). A heuristic proof follows from the comment to A193507 and the first reference there.
link: Alois P. Heinz, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
